domainElements.description: Copy the selected elements to the mouse location.
Copy selected elements from the current diagram into the paste buffer.
Form the composite of the selected morphisms.
Show the string graphs of the morphisms.

Show the new morphism toolbar with the chosen domain and
codomain corresponding to the two selected objects.
Form the hom action on two objects or two morphisms.
Create an identity from the selected object.
Form the product of the selected objects or morphisms.
Form the coproduct of the selected objects or morphisms.
Show the help info for the selected element.
The morphism is to represent a reference in an assembly.
Paste the contents of the paste buffer at the curosor.
If morphisms are selected, delete their objects as well if possible.

Place terminal object at mouse location.  If an object is selected, then a morphism is
placed from that object to the terminal object.
Close toolbar, close panels, change view mode between single diagram view (for editing) and multi-diagram view.
In multi-diagram viewing, the current diagram’s Z-order in the view changes up or down accordingly.
Press the spacebar and move the mouse to pan the current diagram’s view.
If one element is selected, then select the next element of the same type.
If one element is selected, then select the prior element of the same type.

If nothing selected, place object '2' at mouse location.  If an object A or morphism m is
selected, then AxA or mxm is placed.
Possibly undo the last edit action.

If nothing selected, pan in the indicated direction for either single or multi-diagram viewing. 
Otherwise move the selected elements.
